      <h1>Welcome to Taneth</h1>
      <p>This is the build guide for the awesome mega-build Taneth on the Reddit PVE Server.</p>
	  <h2>Taneth History</h2>
	  <p>Before the Great War Taneth was the one of the most powerful cities in all the land, the credit <br/>
	  for that mostly goes to Warriors of Taneth. A stronger, more fierce warrior you will not find anywhere. <br/>
	  However the brawn of the warriors were no match for the magical spells cast down upon us by the dark <br/>
	  wizards from the other realm. They ripped our entire city from its foundation and broke it into pieces <br/>
	  scattered across the land.</p>
	  
	  <p>Once the war subsided ___ the King and the only warrior we had left, a young boy named _____ - Son <br/> 
	  of _______ Champion of Taneth set out on a quest to find _______ the Wise Warlock. Together they were <br/>
	  able to gather the pieces of Taneth and place them on the mountainside here where they rest today.</p>

	  <br/>
	  
	  <h2>Taneth Community</h2>
	  
	  <p>First and foremost, lets remember that this is a community project intended to be fun <br/>
	  for all involved. That being said, all materials are going to be community property, at <br/>
	  least until the main build is done. We want to keep all diamond ore in the ground until we get <br/> 
	  a Fortune III iron pick axe to grab it with. If we wait on it, there will be plenty of diamond to go around.</p>
	  
	  
	  <h2>Task List</h2>
	  
	  <ol>
		<li>Get on Mumble!</li>
		<li>Find Location for Castle - Ideally a Hills Biome so we can put castle on Hill</li>
		<li>Build Mine Entrance and Storage/Smelting Room</li>
		<li>Layout Castle Foundation using Stone Bricks</li>
		<li>Animal Farm - Need Cattle and Sheep</li>
		<li>Food - Wheat - Sugar Cane - Watermelon - Pumpkins</li>
		<li>Figure Rough plan for roads and bridges out of main castle</li>
		<li>Start laying out Farms</li>
		<li>Once Castle is done - layout plots for buildings in the city</li>
	  </ol>
	  
	  <h2>Materials Needed:</h2>
	  <ul>
	  <li>Wood - Tools and Fences and Torches - possibly make charcoal</li>
	  <li>Smooth Stone</li>
	  <li>Stone Brick</li>
	  <li>Sand (for Glass Panes)</li>
	  <li>Wool (white and blue currently)</li>
	  <li>Red Wool for inside keep</li>
	  <li>Glowstone - this might be tricky</li>
	  <li>Cocoa Beans and Netherwarts (not a priority)</li>
	  </ul
	  
	  
